    "prompt": "<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"passage\"><div class=\"prose style:1\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a box in three orientations, labeled X, Y, and Z, on a table. In orientation X, the face on the table is composed of the length and width, and has the greatest surface area touching the table. In orientation Y, the face on the table is composed of the length and height. In orientation Z, the face on the table is composed of the width and height.\" src=\"/images/566395642effeeab83d01d31ae8f6893.svg\"></div></div></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A rectangular box of uniform density can be placed on a table in any of the three orientations shown in the figure. The surface area of the box touching the table in each orientation is <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A sub X\"><math alttext=\"A sub X\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>A</mi><mtext>X</mtext></msub></math></span></span>, <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A sub Y\"><math alttext=\"A sub Y\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>A</mi><mtext>Y</mtext></msub></math></span></span>, <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A sub Z\"><math alttext=\"A sub Z\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>A</mi><mtext>Z</mtext></msub></math></span></span>, for orientation <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"X\"><math alttext=\"X\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">X</mi></math></span></span>, <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Y\"><math alttext=\"Y\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Y</mi></math></span></span>, and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Z\"><math alttext=\"Z\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Z</mi></math></span></span>, respectively, where <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A sub X is greater tha